## Understanding

This issue ports four core engine modules from `scripts/loop.sh` (bash) to TypeScript in `src/lib/`: agent spawning, git worktree management, GitHub CLI helpers, and prompt building. These are the building blocks that the main loop (issue #76) will compose. The `src/lib/` directory doesn't exist yet — this creates it. Dependencies on #73 (CLI scaffold) and #74 (utility subcommands for `shell.ts`) mean `shell.ts` must provide `exec()` and `run()` functions that these modules call.

## Acceptance Criteria

### Agent Runner (`src/lib/agent.ts`)
- [ ] `spawnAgent()` with `agent: 'claude'` constructs args: `claude -p --model X --max-turns N --dangerously-skip-permissions --verbose --output-format text`
- [ ] `spawnAgent()` with `agent: 'codex'` constructs args: `codex -q --model X --auto-edit`
- [ ] `spawnAgent()` with `agent: 'opencode'` constructs args: `opencode run --model X`
- [ ] Prompt piped via stdin (like `echo "$prompt" | claude -p`)
- [ ] Output streams to terminal in real-time via `spawn` (not buffered `exec`)
- [ ] Full output captured and returned in `AgentResult.output`
- [ ] `AgentResult.duration` tracks wall-clock ms accurately
- [ ] `logFile` option writes output to file (like bash `tee`)
- [ ] Non-zero exit code doesn't throw — returned in `AgentResult.exitCode`
- [ ] Logs agent name, model, and cwd before spawning (matches loop.sh line 1853 pattern)

### Worktree Manager (`src/lib/worktree.ts`)
- [ ] `setupWorktree()` creates worktree at `{projectDir}/../issue-{num}` with branch `agent/issue-{num}`
- [ ] Branches from `sessionBranch` when `autoMerge=true` AND session branch exists (origin or local)
- [ ] Branches from `baseBranch` when `autoMerge=false` or session branch doesn't exist
- [ ] Cleans up existing worktree+branch before creating new one (loop.sh:766-770)
- [ ] Deletes remote branch from previous failed runs (loop.sh:773)
- [ ] Fetches origin before creating worktree (loop.sh:794)
- [ ] Falls back to local branch if `origin/X` doesn't work (loop.sh:798-805)
- [ ] Copies `.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.development`, `.env.development.local` files (loop.sh:808-813)
- [ ] Runs `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` (fallback to `pnpm install`) unless `skipInstall=true`
- [ ] `cleanupWorktree()` removes worktree but keeps branch
- [ ] `cleanupWorktree()` force-removes + prunes on failure (loop.sh:845-849)
- [ ] `cleanupWorktree()` skips if `autoCleanup=false`
- [ ] Dry run mode logs without acting

### GitHub Helpers (`src/lib/github.ts`)
- [ ] `pollIssues()` returns `Issue[]` with number, title, body, labels from `gh issue list --json`
- [ ] `labelIssue()` adds and optionally removes labels via `gh issue edit`
- [ ] `commentIssue()` posts comment via `gh issue comment`
- [ ] `createPR()` pushes branch, creates PR via `gh pr create`, returns URL
- [ ] `createPR()` detects existing PR via `gh pr list --head` and updates via `gh pr edit`
- [ ] `createPR()` truncates review body at 30k chars (loop.sh:2443-2446)
- [ ] `mergePR()` merges with `--squash --delete-branch` by default
- [ ] `mergePR()` creates session branch if needed before merging (loop.sh:2521-2533)
- [ ] `updateProjectStatus()` updates GitHub Project board status field
- [ ] All functions handle `gh` CLI errors with clear error messages
- [ ] Dry run support where applicable

### Prompt Builder (`src/lib/prompts.ts`)
- [ ] `buildImplementPrompt()` produces prompt matching loop.sh:1260-1289
- [ ] Optional sections (vision, project context, previous result, learning) omitted when empty
- [ ] `buildReviewPrompt()` includes full 4-section checklist (Functional Completeness, Integration Gaps, Code Quality, UX Review)
- [ ] `buildReviewPrompt()` includes Actions section with CRITICAL/WARNING/INFO severity levels
- [ ] `buildLearnPrompt()` includes all run metadata (issue, status, retries, duration, date)
- [ ] `buildLearnPrompt()` includes all input sections (requirements, diff, test output, review, verification)
- [ ] All prompts are pure functions with no side effects

## Implementation Plan

### Step 1: Create `src/lib/agent.ts`
- Export `AgentResult` type: `{ exitCode: number; output: string; duration: number }`
- Export `spawnAgent()` async function using `node:child_process` `spawn`
- Build CLI args via a switch on `options.agent` ('claude' | 'codex' | 'opencode')
- Write prompt to stdin, pipe stdout/stderr to both `process.stdout` and a buffer (tee behavior)
- If `logFile` provided, also write to a `node:fs` write stream
- Track duration with `Date.now()` before/after
- Resolve promise on `close` event with structured `AgentResult`
- Reference: `reference/cli-runner.reference.ts` for process lifecycle patterns (SIGTERM/SIGKILL, event handling)

### Step 2: Create `src/lib/worktree.ts`
- Export `WorktreeResult` type: `{ path: string; branch: string }`
- Export `setupWorktree()` — uses `exec()` from `shell.ts` for all git commands
- Implement the full setup sequence: cleanup existing → delete remote branch → fetch → determine source branch → `git worktree add` with fallback → copy `.env` files → `pnpm install`
- Export `cleanupWorktree()` — remove worktree, force fallback with `rm -rf` + `git worktree prune`
- Reference: `reference/worktree-manager.reference.ts` for retry logic on git locks, safety validation, `copyEnvFilesToWorktree()`

### Step 3: Create `src/lib/github.ts`
- Export `Issue` type and all helper functions
- All functions use `exec()` from `shell.ts` to call `gh` CLI
- `pollIssues()`: `gh issue list --repo X --label Y --state open --json number,title,body,labels`
- `labelIssue()`: `gh issue edit N --repo X --add-label Y [--remove-label Z]`
- `commentIssue()`: `gh issue comment N --repo X --body Y`
- `createPR()`: check for existing PR first, then create or update. Include PR body template from loop.sh:2460-2486
- `mergePR()`: find PR by branch, create session branch if needed, `gh pr merge --squash --delete-branch`
- `updateProjectStatus()`: complex multi-step `gh project` commands (item lookup → field lookup → item-edit)
- Reference: `reference/github-client.reference.ts` for error handling patterns

### Step 4: Create `src/lib/prompts.ts`
- Pure string template functions, no imports needed beyond standard lib
- `buildImplementPrompt()`: template literal with conditional sections using ternary/filter
- `buildReviewPrompt()`: template literal with full checklist from loop.sh:1309-1353
- `buildLearnPrompt()`: template literal with frontmatter and all analysis sections from loop.sh:1369-1416
- Each optional section only included when the corresponding parameter is truthy/non-empty

### Step 5: Create tests
- `tests/lib/agent.test.ts` — mock `node:child_process` `spawn`, verify arg construction for each agent type, verify output capture, verify duration tracking, verify logFile write
- `tests/lib/worktree.test.ts` — mock `shell.ts` `exec`, verify git command sequences for setup and cleanup, verify autoMerge branching logic, verify env file copy, verify dry run
